/02_fetch_meshes.py#L36) now accepts `--refetch-meshes`, `--refetch-skeletons`, and `--require-skeletons`, writes per-root provenance into the manifest, reports aggregate cache-hit/fetch/failure counts, and preserves existing bundle records on reruns. [03_build_wave_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py#L64) now preserves the raw-fetch provenance when processed assets are built. I also added regression coverage in [tests/test_mesh_pipeline_fetch.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_mesh_pipeline_fetch.py#L44), plus manifest/integration assertions in [tests/test_geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_geometry_contract.py#L52) and [tests/test_config_paths.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_config_paths.py#L72). Config examples were updated with the new knobs in [config/local.yaml](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/config/local.yaml) and [config/visual_subset.example.yaml](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/config/visual_subset.example.yaml).\\n\\nVerified with `make test` and `.venv/bin/python -m unittest tests.test_mesh_pipeline_fetch -v`. Both passed.\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-002_Make_raw_geometry_ingestion_cache-aware_resumable_and_provenance-rich/last_message.md:5:The CLI in [02_fetch_meshes.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py#L36) now accepts `--refetch-meshes`, `--refetch-skeletons`, and `--require-skeletons`, writes per-root provenance into the manifest, reports aggregate cache-hit/fetch/failure counts, and preserves existing bundle records on reruns. [03_build_wave_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_s